    answer:"Use a constrained type when a value itself needs a checked invariant. Use `requires` and `ensures` when the important fact lives on a function boundary instead. Sigil proves both through the same flow-sensitive solver-backed proof fragment, including supported branch facts, exact record patterns, `#`, and direct boolean aliases.",
